; ============================================================================
; Dune package-management workspace for OxCaml  (EXAMPLE / currently BLOCKED)
; ============================================================================
; Following https://dune.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/dune-package-management/oxcaml.html
;
; To try it: rename this file to `dune-workspace`, add the `(package ...)` block
; below to `dune-project`, then run `dune pkg lock`.
;
; STATUS: `dune pkg lock` does NOT currently resolve for this project. The oxcaml
; opam-repository pulls in `oxcaml-patch-guards`, which adds a {post} disjunction
; `oxcaml-<pkg> | oxcaml-<pkg>-patches` for every patchable package. opam defers
; {post} deps, but dune's solver eagerly selects the `oxcaml-<pkg>` guard ("patched
; lib NOT installed"), which then conflicts with the real package our deps require
; (e.g. bignum -> zarith >= 1.12, fmt -> topkg). The solver does not backtrack to the
; `-patches` side, so it fails on zarith/topkg/uutf/spawn/... The tutorial's hello-world
; works only because it never pulls a patched package; bonsai_web + js_of_ocaml always do.
; Until dune's solver handles these {post} disjunctions (or the oxcaml repo changes the
; mechanism), build via the opam switch instead — see docs/dune-package-management.md.
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

(lang dune 3.21)

(pkg enabled)

; The preview packages this project uses (bonsai_web, ppx_html, ppx_css ...) live on the
; `dev` branch, so search it first, then the main oxcaml repo, then upstream (needed for
; leaf packages like angstrom/uri/uucp — the oxcaml repo is an overlay, not a full fork).
(repository
 (name oxcaml-dev)
 (url git+https://github.com/oxcaml/opam-repository#dev))

(repository
 (name oxcaml)
 (url git+https://github.com/oxcaml/opam-repository))

(lock_dir
 (repositories oxcaml-dev oxcaml upstream))

; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Add this to dune-project (the `-patches` markers are an attempt to force the
; "installed" side of the guard disjunction — necessary but still not sufficient
; given the solver limitation above):
;
; (package
;  (name avalon-bonsai)
;  (depends
;   (ocaml-variants (= 5.2.0+ox))
;   core bonsai bonsai_web virtual_dom
;   js_of_ocaml js_of_ocaml-ppx js_of_ocaml-compiler
;   ppx_jane ppx_css ppx_html
;   oxcaml-zarith-patches oxcaml-topkg-patches oxcaml-uutf-patches
;   oxcaml-spawn-patches oxcaml-yojson-patches oxcaml-re-patches
;   oxcaml-sedlex-patches oxcaml-ppxlib-patches oxcaml-ppxlib_ast-patches
;   oxcaml-ppx_deriving-patches oxcaml-gen_js_api-patches oxcaml-ojs-patches
;   oxcaml-js_of_ocaml-patches oxcaml-js_of_ocaml-ppx-patches
;   oxcaml-js_of_ocaml-compiler-patches oxcaml-ocamlfind-patches
;   oxcaml-ocaml-compiler-libs-patches oxcaml-ocamlc-loc-patches))
